      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De desperatione</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e104">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e112">Diffidentiae quodammodo genus est, contra hoc
              quod quisque praedicat torqueri moestitia.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e127">Praesumptio virtutis propriae tanto gravius in
              desperatione est, quanto longius ab humilitate.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e134">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e142">Gravi desperationis telo mens percutitur, cum
              supernae irae tribulationibus premitur, et linguarum foris opprobriis urgetur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e149">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e157">Clausis oculis cordis eo anima praecipitatur in
              infimis, quo obscuratur a summis; et tanto securius mala temporalia perpetrat, quanto
              durius bona aeterna desperat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e165">Gregorius, in <title>Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e173">Deus hominem, quem benigne condidit, inique non
              spernit. Pensandum est igitur, quanti est periculi transacta munera cernere, et futura
              desperare.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e178">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e188" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e180">Joannes Chrysostomus, in <title>Sermonibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e188">Utrumque periculosum est, et confidentia
              perversa, et desperatio. Nam confidentia nimia stantem evertit; et desperatio post
              lapsum non permittit exsurgere.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e193">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e203" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e195">Augustinus, <title>de Poenitentia</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e203">Qui de Deo non praesumit veniam, non
              animadvertit plus peccato suo posse Dei clementiam.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-d1e208">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e218" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Rd1e210">Isidorus, <title>in Synonymis</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31440-Qd1e218">Non desperes de salute, si ad meliora
              converteris: qui enim veniam de peccato desperat, plus se desperatione, quam commisso
              scelere damnat. Desperatio namque auget peccatum, et pejor est omni peccato.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
